	<presentation id="change-management">
		<title>Change Management and Versioning</title>
		<toc class="abstract">Like everything on a long-enough timeline, APIs do change over time. Having a plan for how change is managed, and encouraging API designs that are better at dealing with changes can make a big difference for the effectiveness of an API landscape.</toc>
		<toc class="resources"><a href="https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6648" title="RFC 6648: 'Deprecating the &quot;X-&quot; Prefix and Similar Constructs in Application Protocols', June 2012">RFC 6648</a>&#160;· <a href="http://dret.typepad.com/dretblog/2016/04/robust-extensibility.html" title='Erik Wilde, "Patterns for Robust Extensibility", April 2016'>Robust Extensibility</a>&#160;· <a href="https://blog.goodapi.co/api-change-management-2fe5bba32e9b" title='Zdenek Nemec, "API Change Management", April 2017'>Change Management</a>&#160;· <a href="http://semver.org/" title='Semantic Versioning 2.0.0'>Semantic Versioning</a></toc>
